
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `desktop-file-edit` baraye tagheer dadan file-haye `.desktop` be kar miravad. File-haye `.desktop` baraye ijad launcher-ha (icon-ha) dar menu-ha va rooye safe desktop estefade mishavand. Ba in dastoor mitoonid nam, dastoor, va icon-haye launcher-ha ro tagheer bedid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--create` --> ✨ Yek file `.desktop` jadid misazad.
    🔹 `--desktop-file NAME` --> 📂 Esme file `.desktop` ke mikhahid tagheer bedid ro moshakhas mikonad.
    🔹 `--set-name VALUE` --> 🏷️ Name launcher ro tagheer mide.
    🔹 `--set-icon VALUE` --> 🖼️ Icon launcher ro tagheer mide.
    🔹 `--set-exec VALUE` --> 🚀 Dastoori ke ba ejraye launcher ejra mishe ro tagheer mide.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ desktop-file-edit --desktop-file myapp.desktop --set-name "My Application"

    🔹 Name launcher "myapp.desktop" ra be "My Application" tagheer midahad.

    $ desktop-file-edit --desktop-file myapp.desktop --set-icon /path/to/icon.png

    🔹 Icon launcher "myapp.desktop" ra tagheer midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ desktop-file-edit --desktop-file myapp.desktop --set-exec "my_application_script.sh"

    🔹  Dastoori ke ba click rooye launcher "myapp.desktop" ejra mishe, be "my_application_script.sh" tagheer peyda mikone.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `desktop-file-edit` command is used to modify `.desktop` files.  `.desktop` files are used to create launchers (icons) in menus and on the desktop.  With this command, you can change the name, execution command, and icons of launchers.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--create` --> ✨ Creates a new `.desktop` file.
    🔹 `--desktop-file NAME` --> 📂 Specifies the name of the `.desktop` file you want to modify.
    🔹 `--set-name VALUE` --> 🏷️ Changes the name of the launcher.
    🔹 `--set-icon VALUE` --> 🖼️ Changes the icon of the launcher.
    🔹 `--set-exec VALUE` --> 🚀 Changes the command that is executed when the launcher is run.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ desktop-file-edit --desktop-file myapp.desktop --set-name "My Application"

    🔹 Changes the name of the "myapp.desktop" launcher to "My Application".

    $ desktop-file-edit --desktop-file myapp.desktop --set-icon /path/to/icon.png

    🔹 Changes the icon of the "myapp.desktop" launcher.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ desktop-file-edit --desktop-file myapp.desktop --set-exec "my_application_script.sh"

    🔹 The command that is executed when clicking the "myapp.desktop" launcher is changed to "my_application_script.sh".
